        "timestamp": "2020-03-05 16:45:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n> \n> > (3 comments)\n>  > \n>  > Then I think delete the legacy policy examples and provide simple\n>  > examples on the latest Policy Types - folks please confirm/help me\n>  > with this as this requires some work in XACML PDP.\n> \n> It is OK with me to delete.   Not sure how CLAMP may be impacted.   I don't think the interface in PDP-D APPS to invoke guard changes in any way, right?\n\nNo the interface is exactly the same, but I am changing the ugly field names. Not a big change just the LHS property names, I'll submit the fixes for it.\n\nI think for CLAMP since they never really used the old TOSCA policy types for guard, but rather sent a similar JSON as the operational policy with \"content\" property containing the old guard attributes, they should be fine. As long as I get the new onap.policies.guard.Common attributes to match TOSCA (which is what this JIRA is all about).",
        "patchset_number": 2
